cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling maintenance on arcs of a capacitated network to maximize flow from a source node to a sink node over time periods. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and identifies relevant characteristics for instance classes. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with scheduling and optimization problems. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and identifies relevant characteristics for instance classes, which can be seen as game-theoretic considerations. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with maximizing flow over time periods, which can be seen as an information-theoretic problem.
